xity in all areas. The world of meaning constructed by the social operating system is a mixed reality in which filters and layers replace the physical restraints of space and time as parameters of knowing and acting. Society and nature, humans and non-humans come together in a socio-sphere consisting of hybrid, heterogeneous actor-networks. This book proposes reinterpreting hermeneutics as networking and networking as guided by a social operating system whose norms are based on new media. There emerges a theory for a global network society described by different concepts than those typical of Western modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aActor-network theory. 0aInformation society. 0aInformation technologyxSocial aspects. 0aSocial networks. 0aSocial sciencesxPhilosophy. 4aActor-Network Theory. 4aConstructivism. 4aDigital Media. 4aDigital Society. 4aInternet. 4aMedia Studies. 4aMedia Theory. 4aNetwork Society. 4aNew Media. 4aPhilosophy. 4aSocial Relations. 4aSocial Theory. 4aSociological Theory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aActor-Network Theory.  aConstructivism.  aDigital Media.  aDigital Society.  aInternet.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Theory.  aNetwork Society.  aNew Media.  aPhilosophy.  aSocial Relations.  aSocial Theory.  aSociological Theory.1 aBelliger, Andréa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066155208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839428115zCo-access DOI 